Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of
water with 1/2 @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Quarter, core and grate the @apple{1}(quartered, cored and grated) (no need to peel).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).
Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (peel first if you
prefer).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{10%g}, grated apple,
@dried rosemary{1%sachet}, @salt{1/4%tsp} for the breadcrumbs (see pantry for amount)
and half the garlic, then add the @British pork mince{240%g}.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into
evenly-sized balls, 5 per person. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a large #baking tray{}. When the oven is hot, bake on the
top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT:
The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip
a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
on medium heat.

When hot, add the @shredded Savoy cabbage{150%g}(shredded) and remaining
garlic and stir-fry for ~{2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{},
add a splash of @water{1%splash}, mix well and cover with a #lid{} (or some
#foil{}). Cook until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the cabbage to a bowl and cover with tin foil to keep warm.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.
Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off
the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} (if you have any) and
mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @ground black
pepper{}. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @sugar{1/4%tsp} for the onions (see pantry for
amount) to the onion pan and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add the @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @water{100%ml} for the gravy (see pantry
for amount).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. TIP: If you're feeling decadent, add
a knob of butter (if you have any).

Add your cooked meatballs to the sauce and gently turn to coat. Warm for ~{1-2%minutes},
then remove from the heat.

Serve the meatballs and red wine gravy with the mash and cabbage alongside.

Enjoy!